1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,560
(The following content may not be
suitable for viewers under 15.)

2
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:05,460
(Viewer discretion is advised.)

3
00:00:07,030 --> 00:00:08,130
Dong Moon.

4
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:11,600
What?

5
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:14,010
Why aren't you saying that?

6
00:00:17,380 --> 00:00:18,440
What?

7
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:21,110
"Do you want to get pastries?"

8
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:23,550
- That.
- That was...

9
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:27,190
sort of like my strategy
when I liked you...

10
00:00:28,390 --> 00:00:29,850
as a girl.

11
00:00:30,590 --> 00:00:31,720
As a girl?

12
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:34,790
Then what? Am I a boy now?

13
00:00:34,790 --> 00:00:36,090
That's not it.

14
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,430
You said before...

15
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,770
that I was a nuisance.

16
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:45,600
You shouldn't eat with
someone who's a nuisance.

17
00:00:47,310 --> 00:00:48,770
Eat with someone you like.

18
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:50,040
I said that...

19
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,980
just out of anger.

20
00:00:55,450 --> 00:00:57,980
Friends can sometimes...

21
00:00:58,020 --> 00:00:59,750
be a nuisance...

22
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:01,850
and stuff. No?

23
00:01:04,390 --> 00:01:06,390
- Friends?
- Yes, friends.

24
00:01:06,730 --> 00:01:09,690
Let's not be a boy and girl,

25
00:01:09,830 --> 00:01:11,500
but real friends.

26
00:01:21,940 --> 00:01:23,540
Okay, good. Friends.

27
00:01:23,610 --> 00:01:26,040
Buns. I'll treat you to
the sweet buns you like.

28
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,050
Let go.

29
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,360
What?

30
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:42,030
I saw it with my own eyes.

31
00:01:42,030 --> 00:01:44,800
Your husband and your maid...

32
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,630
were looking at each other...

33
00:01:47,870 --> 00:01:51,500
with puppy eyes.

34
00:02:02,610 --> 00:02:05,450
Eun Ja, you watch...

35
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:07,350
way too many dramas.

36
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:08,950
No, that's not true.

37
00:02:09,290 --> 00:02:10,390
I saw them.

38
00:02:10,390 --> 00:02:11,960
Do Ha...

39
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:15,360
had something happen to her parents.

40
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:18,930
My husband went with her...

41
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,300
to solve it.

42
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:21,930
Is that what happened?

43
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:25,270
My husband might have a bad temper,

44
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:28,040
but he's the best in town...

45
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:31,080
when working with hard documents.

46
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,080
- Yes.
- Yes.

47
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:34,350
Eun Ja, come on.

48
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:38,080
You should know what you're talking about.

49
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:40,450
My husband is a penny pincher,

50
00:02:40,450 --> 00:02:44,490
so it would be too hard
for him to cheat on me.

51
00:02:44,490 --> 00:02:46,220
- That's true.
- Yes.

52
00:02:46,220 --> 00:02:47,230
Yes.

53
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:52,560
Do Ha, why are you always cleaning that?

54
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,400
It gets rusty.

55
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,330
I have to clean it every day.

56
00:02:56,330 --> 00:02:57,600
Where did the bedpan go?

57
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,140
Dad took it in.

58
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:02,110
Your dad? What's gotten into him?

59
00:03:02,110 --> 00:03:04,980
Why weren't you careful?

60
00:03:04,980 --> 00:03:07,910
Don't get hurt. Don't.

61
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,280
Auntie.

62
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:12,650
Today, at Hyangcheon-dong...

63
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:24,600
Don't complain because I'm making you...

64
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,570
work on a Sunday since Chuseok is coming.

65
00:03:27,570 --> 00:03:28,900
Work properly.

66
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:30,870
Don't make any defects.

67
00:03:30,870 --> 00:03:32,440
- Okay.
- Okay.

68
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,440
Give it to me.

69
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,950
Because you're working on a Sunday,

70
00:03:42,950 --> 00:03:44,550
we feed you lunch and dinner,

71
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:46,080
and we give you extra pay.

72
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,790
Go and ask around.

73
00:03:48,790 --> 00:03:50,960
You wouldn't find a place
that treats you so well.

74
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:55,130
Gosh. Enough showing off.

75
00:03:55,130 --> 00:03:57,930
They can't work because you talk too much.

76
00:03:57,930 --> 00:04:00,500
I'm busy. Why are you
screaming after going out?

77
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,530
I came back really fast.

78
00:04:02,530 --> 00:04:04,440
I didn't even have jajangmyeon.

79
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,070
Why now?

80
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:07,970
You should have had one if
you pay for membership.

81
00:04:07,970 --> 00:04:11,080
Everyone! I'll make pork...

82
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,880
for dinner tonight,

83
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:15,150
so let's do our best today.

84
00:04:16,780 --> 00:04:18,820
Pork? What pork?

85
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:20,390
Be quiet!

86
00:04:22,650 --> 00:04:23,890
Great!

87
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:26,420
Let's go.

88
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:30,300
Did you go see your lover or something?

89
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,800
You're in such a good mood.

90
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,130
Excellent!

91
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:50,080
You startled me.

92
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:52,250
Kyo Ryun.

93
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:55,950
What do you need today?

94
00:04:55,950 --> 00:04:57,190
Today...

95
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:05,200
Shim Ae Sook.

96
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,370
Why are you dressed like that?

97
00:05:09,230 --> 00:05:10,300
What about you?

98
00:05:12,970 --> 00:05:15,570
Hey, how long is it until you're done?

99
00:05:17,110 --> 00:05:18,840
Give me something for my headache.

100
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:20,750
Let me go. She's staring at us.

101
00:05:31,590 --> 00:05:33,490
Hae Joo.

102
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:34,760
Teacher.

103
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:38,430
Gimbap?

104
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,300
Here you go.

105
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,940
How much is it?

106
00:05:47,170 --> 00:05:48,410
Don't worry about it.

107
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:50,140
It's on me.

108
00:05:51,410 --> 00:05:52,810
Goodnight.

109
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:58,450
What are you doing? Go.

110
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,520
- Bye.
- Take care.

111
00:06:01,690 --> 00:06:03,120
Go home!

112
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:08,090
It's hectic, isn't it?

113
00:06:08,090 --> 00:06:09,090
Yes.

114
00:06:14,570 --> 00:06:18,440
Dad wanted some gimbap.

115
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:23,170
I thought of Eng Cho while making it.

116
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:26,710
There isn't a picnic, so why gimbap?

117
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,210
A...

118
00:06:30,650 --> 00:06:31,680
picnic?

119
00:06:54,870 --> 00:06:57,780
- You made so much.
- Have some.

120
00:06:57,880 --> 00:07:01,080
Do Ha, sit down and join us.

121
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,410
- Okay.
- Yes.

122
00:07:02,410 --> 00:07:04,520
Hurry up and eat.

123
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,890
Bong Soo is going to eat all of the meat.

124
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:08,250
Mom.

125
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,520
I'll make a quick trip to the kitchen.

126
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,090
Enough, enough. Sit down.

127
00:07:11,090 --> 00:07:12,420
Sit and eat.

128
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:15,930
- Sit.
- Come sit here.

129
00:07:29,340 --> 00:07:33,680
There are drinks and meat,

130
00:07:33,810 --> 00:07:35,480
but there's no music.

131
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,120
Sing us a song.

132
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,980
- Yes.
- Wow.

133
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,690
I can't sing.

134
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:43,820
Mom, I'm a good singer.

135
00:07:43,820 --> 00:07:46,060
- Forget you.
- Just be quiet.

136
00:07:46,060 --> 00:07:47,260
Sing a song!

137
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:48,990
I can't.

138
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:51,160
Just sing one.

139
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:00,340
You told me you'd come to me

140
00:08:00,340 --> 00:08:04,810
When flowers bloom in spring

141
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:10,820
Like a singing swallow

142
00:08:12,780 --> 00:08:15,650
When I go up on the hill

143
00:08:15,650 --> 00:08:19,860
The chirping cheers me up

144
00:08:19,990 --> 00:08:26,200
It's telling us that spring is coming

145
00:08:26,770 --> 00:08:30,040
However

146
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:34,040
You haven't come back

147
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:37,710
I'm standing on the hill

148
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:41,250
Alone again today

149
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:46,950
While looking at the blue sky

150
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:51,060
I'm reminded of you

151
00:08:54,090 --> 00:08:55,460
Jin.

152
00:08:56,530 --> 00:09:00,570
Did you get to Seoul by now?

153
00:09:01,070 --> 00:09:05,400
You haven't come back

154
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:07,470
I'm standing on the hill

155
00:09:07,810 --> 00:09:08,940
Hey.

156
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:11,940
What are you doing here
after skipping dinner?

157
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,080
I don't have an appetite.

158
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,550
No appetite?

159
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,480
Hey.

160
00:09:20,290 --> 00:09:22,420
Do you want some money? Here.

161
00:09:22,420 --> 00:09:23,460
Did you drink?

162
00:09:23,460 --> 00:09:25,490
I had a drink. Here.

163
00:09:25,490 --> 00:09:26,990
Did something good happen?

164
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:30,760
Your mom is having...

165
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:33,030
an excellent day.

166
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:36,100
However

167
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:41,170
You haven't come back

168
00:09:41,170 --> 00:09:42,340
How lucky.

169
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:45,140
I'm sad today.

170
00:09:46,650 --> 00:09:48,780
- Why?
- You don't have to know.

171
00:09:48,780 --> 00:09:50,750
Rubbish.

172
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,080
What about you?

173
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,020
What good thing happened to you?

174
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:55,890
You don't have to know either.

175
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:14,840
Hello.

176
00:10:15,110 --> 00:10:17,740
I'm Bae Dong Moon from class five.

177
00:10:18,580 --> 00:10:21,910
I heard I received a registered mail.

178
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,110
Hold on.

179
00:10:32,260 --> 00:10:34,030
(Son Jin)

180
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:35,090
Son Jin?

181
00:10:36,130 --> 00:10:37,200
What's this?

182
00:10:42,470 --> 00:10:43,470
Bae Dong Moon.

183
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,570
Are you studying well?

184
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:47,610
How is Jung Hee?

185
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:49,170
Gosh.

186
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:51,440
I'm sending you...

187
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,880
my phone number in Seoul.

188
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:55,610
If you...

189
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:58,080
ever need me,

190
00:10:58,520 --> 00:10:59,880
please call me.

191
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:03,860
Son Jin.

192
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:05,360
What are you doing?

193
00:11:05,990 --> 00:11:07,760
You shouldn't talk if you left.

194
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:33,350
What now?

195
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:34,420
Nothing.

196
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:37,790
Why is my nose so itchy?

197
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:52,000
Just tell me. Don't write to me.

198
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,200
Look at it.

199
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,410
(Son Jin)

200
00:12:00,980 --> 00:12:02,880
What do you want me to do?

201
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:05,280
In it,

202
00:12:06,180 --> 00:12:08,450
there's a number for Jin's home in Seoul.

203
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,260
You can refer to it,

204
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,490
or throw it out.

205
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:16,660
Let's finish here for today.

206
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,630
Okay. We studied too much.

207
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:24,070
I need to sleep now. I'm so sleepy.

208
00:12:28,170 --> 00:12:29,310
Dong Moon,

209
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,480
what do you want me to do with this?

210
00:12:43,420 --> 00:12:44,660
No.

211
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,760
Not this either.

212
00:12:57,470 --> 00:13:00,670
(Son Jin)

213
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,970
Yes.

214
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:05,780
He left, so I should forget him.

215
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:08,710
Are you crazy?

216
00:13:09,980 --> 00:13:11,880
What is that?

217
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,690
Why did you put away the bedpan?

218
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:17,490
Don't pee in the bedpan anymore.

219
00:13:17,490 --> 00:13:19,990
We have a washroom.

220
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:21,890
Why would you pee in the room?

221
00:13:21,890 --> 00:13:24,000
- It smells bad.
- It smells?

222
00:13:24,830 --> 00:13:26,800
You stood through it all these years.

223
00:13:27,070 --> 00:13:29,570
- Why now?
- If you want it,

224
00:13:29,570 --> 00:13:31,200
then you can bring it down yourself.

225
00:13:31,570 --> 00:13:32,600
What?

226
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,710
Hey. Hey...

227
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:38,180
What's with her?

228
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,310
How strange.

229
00:13:40,810 --> 00:13:42,080
Gosh.

230
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,630
He's coming, he's coming!

231
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:58,630
- They're coming.
- What?

232
00:13:58,660 --> 00:14:00,700
- He's so handsome.
- Look.

233
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:04,040
- Is he human?
- He's so hot.

234
00:14:04,470 --> 00:14:05,670
I'm dying.

235
00:14:06,170 --> 00:14:07,840
- Me too.
- Seriously.

236
00:14:08,310 --> 00:14:09,370
Jung Hee.

237
00:14:11,610 --> 00:14:12,610
Yes?

238
00:14:15,610 --> 00:14:17,380
Did something happen?

239
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:21,490
We did well on our exam,
but you weren't happy.

240
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,890
Is it because of Jin?

241
00:14:27,230 --> 00:14:28,560
No, it's not because of him.

242
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,330
When I was 10,

243
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:38,100
my mom passed away.

244
00:14:38,740 --> 00:14:40,270
She was really sick.

245
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:42,770
My mom told me this.

246
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:46,410
If you fall in love, you become brave.

247
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,850
I didn't know what she meant back then,

248
00:14:49,850 --> 00:14:53,350
but I think I'm starting to understand her.

249
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:56,920
You become brave when you fall in love?

250
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:58,060
Yes.

251
00:14:59,660 --> 00:15:01,860
Jung Hee,

252
00:15:02,590 --> 00:15:05,760
if I had someone I desperately missed,

253
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:07,400
I'd go and see them.

254
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:11,000
It wouldn't matter where they are.

255
00:15:16,980 --> 00:15:19,380
No matter where they are?

256
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:21,450
Yes.

257
00:15:28,090 --> 00:15:31,290
You become brave when you fall in love?

258
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:34,630
That means...

259
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:38,630
I shouldn't stand through this heartache.

260
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,110
(Son Jin)

261
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:51,980
Auntie.

262
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:54,350
Please, just this once.

263
00:15:54,710 --> 00:15:56,480
Your mom will be mad if she finds out.

264
00:15:56,620 --> 00:15:58,120
It's Saturday tomorrow,

265
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,620
so tell her I'm at Eun Ja's.

266
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,520
All you have to do is
stop her from calling.

267
00:16:02,850 --> 00:16:06,020
I'm going to be right
back after seeing Jin.

268
00:16:06,220 --> 00:16:08,190
Please, Auntie.

269
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,230
Fine.

270
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:14,200
However, you have to be careful.

271
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:16,270
Auntie, thank you.

272
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,870
You're the best.

273
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:19,500
What should I wear?

274
00:16:29,380 --> 00:16:30,450
Jin.

275
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:33,450
I'm finally coming to see you.

276
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,920
Please wait for me.

277
00:16:48,470 --> 00:16:50,740
Jung Hee, they say...

278
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:52,870
Seoul is full of crooks.

279
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:55,210
Be careful at all times,

280
00:16:55,770 --> 00:16:58,380
and especially of cars and people.

281
00:16:59,180 --> 00:17:00,450
From Auntie.

282
00:17:27,410 --> 00:17:30,280
Jung Hee, stay focused.

283
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:33,410
Don't lose your nose.

284
00:17:37,950 --> 00:17:39,990
I'm sorry. Are you all right?

285
00:17:40,150 --> 00:17:42,020
- I'm okay. Are you?
- I'm sorry.

286
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:44,820
- Yes. I'm sorry.
- No problem.

287
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:50,700
Jung Hee...

288
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:54,730
- went to a friend's?
- Yes.

289
00:17:55,370 --> 00:17:56,770
You can go and study.

290
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:59,900
Did she go to Seoul?

291
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:13,820
My wallet.

292
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:55,930
Why isn't anyone picking up?

293
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:02,870
How many calls are you making?

294
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:07,340
I'm sorry.

295
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:21,150
Son Jin, why aren't you picking up?

296
00:19:22,890 --> 00:19:24,490
How frustrating.

297
00:19:27,630 --> 00:19:29,260
(Son Jin's Seoul contact)

298
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:37,700
I'm hungry, but I don't have money.

299
00:19:41,410 --> 00:19:42,510
Steamed buns.

300
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:44,710
They look good.

301
00:19:44,780 --> 00:19:48,110
Dong Moon likes steamed buns.

302
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,550
Jung Hee.

303
00:19:54,020 --> 00:19:55,090
Dong Moon!

304
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:07,330
Is it because I'm hungry?

305
00:20:08,070 --> 00:20:10,440
Why am I thinking about Dong Moon?

306
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,510
Yes?

307
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:21,950
Dong Moon.

308
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:25,150
Jung Hee?

309
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,020
She didn't come here.

310
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:47,340
I think it's somewhere around here.

311
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:53,550
What do I do? The last bus already left.

312
00:21:01,690 --> 00:21:02,890
No.

313
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:07,560
If I turn back now, walking around Seoul...

314
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:11,000
would have been useless.

315
00:21:14,570 --> 00:21:16,170
It's all or nothing.

316
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:26,950
Excuse me, where are you going?

317
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:30,080
- What is it?
- You're from out of town?

318
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:32,850
- Let's hang out.
- What are you doing?

319
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:33,990
I don't want to!

320
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:35,950
- Come with us.
- Let go!

321
00:21:35,950 --> 00:21:37,720
- Let go!
- Come on.

322
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,660
- What is it?
- Who are you?

323
00:21:43,330 --> 00:21:44,630
Jin.

324
00:21:49,730 --> 00:21:51,300
They're doing raids for
long hair over there.

325
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,640
Darn it.

326
00:22:01,910 --> 00:22:03,110
Jin.

327
00:22:11,660 --> 00:22:13,120
Why are you here?

328
00:22:13,860 --> 00:22:15,990
Do you know how dangerous Seoul is?

329
00:22:16,260 --> 00:22:19,160
Because I wanted to see you.

330
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
I mean...

331
00:22:22,570 --> 00:22:24,940
I missed you and wanted to see you,

332
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,940
so I wanted to check if
my feelings were real.

333
00:22:35,110 --> 00:22:36,110
So?

334
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:38,280
Did you?

335
00:22:40,990 --> 00:22:42,190
I'm not sure.

336
00:22:42,850 --> 00:22:43,860
What?

337
00:22:47,090 --> 00:22:48,160
Nothing.

338
00:22:49,330 --> 00:22:50,930
Now that I saw you,

339
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,400
I'll leave.

340
00:22:53,830 --> 00:22:56,200
It'll be curfew soon.

341
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:00,510
The last train left already.

342
00:23:01,110 --> 00:23:02,210
How will you go home?

343
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:06,410
A relative lives nearby.

344
00:23:08,380 --> 00:23:09,380
For real?

345
00:23:10,980 --> 00:23:11,980
Yes.

346
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:14,520
Okay, then.

347
00:23:15,190 --> 00:23:17,120
Take care.

348
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:19,860
Bye.

349
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,470
Whatever.

350
00:23:27,870 --> 00:23:30,100
I'll sleep at the police station.

351
00:23:30,540 --> 00:23:33,540
I don't want to depend on him.

352
00:23:33,570 --> 00:23:34,740
Jung Hee.

353
00:23:38,410 --> 00:23:39,610
Jung Hee.

354
00:23:42,250 --> 00:23:44,150
Seriously, Jung Hee.

355
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:45,950
Where are you?

356
00:23:47,390 --> 00:23:48,390
But...

357
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:51,660
why is Seoul so empty?

358
00:23:56,330 --> 00:23:57,330
What's that?

359
00:23:58,130 --> 00:23:59,500
Is it curfew already?

360
00:24:06,670 --> 00:24:07,770
Jung Hee.

361
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:11,340
Jung Hee.

362
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:17,680
Why are you out after curfew?

363
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:22,020
Sirs. I...

364
00:24:22,390 --> 00:24:25,190
I'm looking for a friend.

365
00:24:44,210 --> 00:24:46,040
You can't spend the night
at a police station.

366
00:24:47,580 --> 00:24:48,910
Jin.

367
00:24:55,450 --> 00:24:56,450
Come on.

368
00:25:21,850 --> 00:25:24,380
This is my uncle's house.

369
00:25:25,580 --> 00:25:26,790
They went to Daegu...

370
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,550
for a banquet.

371
00:25:28,750 --> 00:25:30,690
They'll be back tomorrow, luckily.

372
00:25:33,290 --> 00:25:34,430
Luckily?

373
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:38,930
Not luckily.

374
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:41,730
Coincidentally.

375
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:52,810
Are you hungry?

376
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:54,050
No.

377
00:25:54,610 --> 00:25:57,480
I ate lunch on the bus.

378
00:25:57,480 --> 00:26:00,020
Lunch was so long ago.

379
00:26:00,590 --> 00:26:02,590
You said you walked here
from the bus terminal.

380
00:26:08,430 --> 00:26:09,430
Okay.

381
00:26:09,730 --> 00:26:10,900
I made three.

382
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:12,430
Eat up.

383
00:26:24,610 --> 00:26:26,580
Eat more. Like this.

384
00:26:31,820 --> 00:26:32,820
See?

385
00:26:33,620 --> 00:26:34,620
Okay.

386
00:26:40,830 --> 00:26:41,830
Is it good?

387
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:45,860
It's strange.

388
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:48,570
I like instant noodles more than anything.

389
00:26:48,570 --> 00:26:50,400
Why does it taste so bad?

390
00:26:55,570 --> 00:26:56,640
Is it good?

391
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,440
Yes.

392
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:01,580
Why is Dong Moon...

393
00:27:07,790 --> 00:27:09,320
To study abroad?

394
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,060
Why so suddenly...

395
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:15,690
My father wanted me...

396
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,700
to go to Seoul University.

397
00:27:19,700 --> 00:27:22,300
But with my grades recently,

398
00:27:23,470 --> 00:27:25,140
he thinks it'll be difficult,

399
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:27,770
so he wants to send me abroad.

400
00:27:28,470 --> 00:27:29,540
And you?

401
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,410
Do you want to go?

402
00:27:41,050 --> 00:27:42,050
Jung Hee.

403
00:27:45,190 --> 00:27:46,220
You thought...

404
00:27:47,430 --> 00:27:49,130
really highly of me.

405
00:27:51,300 --> 00:27:52,360
But you know,

406
00:27:54,730 --> 00:27:55,800
I'm a loser.

407
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:57,670
You didn't know, right?

408
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:00,010
No.

409
00:28:00,170 --> 00:28:02,470
No. You are...

410
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,480
Thanks, Jung Hee,

411
00:28:07,250 --> 00:28:08,580
for liking me.

412
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:18,320
That's right.

413
00:28:18,860 --> 00:28:20,190
Dong Moon...

414
00:28:21,130 --> 00:28:22,560
was very worried about you.

415
00:28:23,260 --> 00:28:24,430
He was?

416
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:25,760
That's right.

417
00:28:26,530 --> 00:28:28,430
Maybe you should call him.

418
00:28:29,430 --> 00:28:31,440
Do you know his number?

419
00:28:33,100 --> 00:28:34,110
But then again,

420
00:28:35,470 --> 00:28:37,580
it's too late to call.

421
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:46,180
I'm dead if Mom and Dad find out.

422
00:28:54,630 --> 00:28:58,060
Jung Hee is sleeping
over at Eun Ja's house?

423
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,830
Yes.

424
00:29:04,870 --> 00:29:05,870
Auntie.

425
00:29:07,010 --> 00:29:08,970
I didn't think of you as a liar.

426
00:29:28,660 --> 00:29:29,860
It may be uncomfortable,

427
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:32,100
but sleep well.

428
00:29:33,060 --> 00:29:34,330
What about you?

429
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:35,600
I can...

430
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:37,540
sleep in the living room.

431
00:29:40,670 --> 00:29:41,740
Good night.

432
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:51,580
Go to bed.

433
00:29:52,980 --> 00:29:53,990
Okay.

434
00:30:18,940 --> 00:30:20,180
Does Jin...

435
00:30:20,910 --> 00:30:22,410
wear glasses?

436
00:30:25,580 --> 00:30:29,290
Dong Moon would look good
with glasses like these.

437
00:30:37,230 --> 00:30:39,130
What's my problem?

438
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:49,270
He must be worried about me.

439
00:30:59,290 --> 00:31:02,530
[VIU Ver] E07 Girls' Generation
1979 "Finding Love" -= Ruo Xi =-

440
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:10,630
You can't sleep?

441
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:13,900
No.

442
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:15,830
I'm sleeping.

443
00:31:16,430 --> 00:31:18,140
Then how are you talking?

444
00:31:22,210 --> 00:31:23,210
Go to sleep.

445
00:31:24,140 --> 00:31:25,780
I'll sing you a lullaby.

446
00:31:34,050 --> 00:31:36,190
Oh Danny Boy

447
00:31:37,620 --> 00:31:39,990
The pipes, the pipes

448
00:31:40,630 --> 00:31:42,860
Are calling

449
00:31:44,030 --> 00:31:46,500
From glen to glen

450
00:31:47,970 --> 00:31:51,770
And down the mountain side

451
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,140
Punks.

452
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:56,510
The summer's gone

453
00:31:58,110 --> 00:32:02,280
And all the roses falling

454
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:06,180
Jung Hee.

455
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:08,820
Where are you?

456
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:12,320
I hope you're okay.

457
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:18,800
I got a strange feeling...

458
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:20,500
at that moment.

459
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:24,440
My first love, Jin.

460
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,940
I missed him so badly...

461
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:31,440
that it made me rush up to Seoul.

462
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:33,040
Jin.

463
00:32:33,350 --> 00:32:36,210
But did I really...

464
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:39,050
in fact like him?

465
00:32:41,550 --> 00:32:44,960
I'm with Jin right now,

466
00:32:45,860 --> 00:32:48,460
so why do I feel empty?

467
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,400
It's strange.

468
00:32:53,530 --> 00:32:55,330
Why am I so confused?

469
00:33:30,770 --> 00:33:31,870
Hae Joo.

470
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:35,970
I love you.

471
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:38,180
Mister.

472
00:33:39,110 --> 00:33:42,080
Should we run away?

473
00:33:44,220 --> 00:33:45,750
Somewhere no one can find us?

474
00:33:47,050 --> 00:33:48,150
Yes,

475
00:33:49,490 --> 00:33:50,620
let's go.

476
00:33:52,190 --> 00:33:53,790
Let's go far away.

477
00:33:55,330 --> 00:33:57,730
Okay. Just trust me.

478
00:34:00,100 --> 00:34:01,130
Let's go.

479
00:34:52,420 --> 00:34:53,620
Young Choon.

480
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,050
Face reality.

481
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:59,060
This is wrong.

482
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:02,530
If you truly love Hae Joo,

483
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:06,030
you can't do this.

484
00:35:17,780 --> 00:35:20,810
Thank you for everything.

485
00:35:21,750 --> 00:35:25,580
Study hard and bring up
your grades during finals.

486
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:27,520
Okay?

487
00:35:29,050 --> 00:35:30,060
Okay.

488
00:35:31,820 --> 00:35:33,020
- And...
- And...

489
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:38,360
You first.

490
00:35:38,660 --> 00:35:39,830
And...

491
00:35:41,370 --> 00:35:45,000
you are definitely not a loser.

492
00:35:46,710 --> 00:35:48,970
When you said that last night...

493
00:35:50,910 --> 00:35:53,280
You're really cool...

494
00:35:53,580 --> 00:35:56,480
and a brave person.

495
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:04,960
What were you about to say?

496
00:36:13,060 --> 00:36:14,170
I was happy...

497
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:17,740
that you came.

498
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:28,310
The bus to Daegu is leaving!

499
00:36:32,650 --> 00:36:33,750
Go on.

500
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:37,990
Okay.

501
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:42,090
Goodbye.

502
00:36:46,130 --> 00:36:47,170
Jung Hee.

503
00:36:57,780 --> 00:36:58,880
I'll see you again.

504
00:37:13,290 --> 00:37:16,330
I couldn't sleep last night. I'm tired.

505
00:37:24,670 --> 00:37:25,700
You...

506
00:37:38,250 --> 00:37:40,550
Where are your glasses?

507
00:37:41,990 --> 00:37:43,150
I lost them.

508
00:37:47,690 --> 00:37:49,630
Where did you sleep last night?

509
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:53,230
At a relative's.

510
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:58,440
What a tearful parting.

511
00:37:58,870 --> 00:38:01,170
I thought you were filming a movie.

512
00:38:01,710 --> 00:38:02,810
What?

513
00:38:05,980 --> 00:38:08,980
Why did you tell me Jin's address...

514
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:10,480
if you were going to do this?

515
00:38:13,590 --> 00:38:14,720
Because...

516
00:38:16,860 --> 00:38:18,360
you were hurt.

517
00:38:20,960 --> 00:38:22,560
I'd rather hurt...

518
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,400
than have you hurting.

519
00:38:36,540 --> 00:38:37,740
I'm hungry.

520
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:41,480
I got it at the terminal.

521
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:43,070
I don't know if it's good.

522
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:44,420
You...

523
00:38:45,580 --> 00:38:47,390
ate with Jin, right?

524
00:38:47,420 --> 00:38:48,820
I'm going to eat my breakfast.

525
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:12,610
Did you starve?

526
00:39:13,710 --> 00:39:15,150
Jin didn't even feed you?

527
00:39:15,910 --> 00:39:17,150
It's strange,

528
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:19,920
but I don't like Seoul food.

529
00:39:28,290 --> 00:39:30,100
It's so strange.

530
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:34,200
Why does everything taste
so good with Dong Moon?

531
00:39:44,580 --> 00:39:45,610
Are you okay?

532
00:39:47,410 --> 00:39:48,910
Eat slowly.

533
00:40:17,210 --> 00:40:18,540
- Are you happy?
- Yes.

534
00:40:18,940 --> 00:40:21,550
I'm so very happy. I love picnics.

535
00:40:26,220 --> 00:40:27,820
Come sit down.

536
00:40:35,990 --> 00:40:38,630
Sit here. You'll get bit.

537
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:40,400
I'm fine.

538
00:40:44,740 --> 00:40:46,300
That stings.

539
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:54,510
Do you like gimbap?

540
00:40:59,050 --> 00:41:00,220
Yummy.

541
00:41:02,050 --> 00:41:03,360
Chew properly.

542
00:41:18,570 --> 00:41:19,570
It tastes good.

543
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:34,820
You heard the rumors, right?

544
00:41:36,150 --> 00:41:38,690
That Eng Cho is my child and stuff.

545
00:41:40,790 --> 00:41:41,790
Yes.

546
00:41:42,690 --> 00:41:43,700
What?

547
00:41:45,430 --> 00:41:46,830
You really did?

548
00:41:48,330 --> 00:41:49,400
Yes.

549
00:41:54,170 --> 00:41:55,670
That's...

550
00:41:56,570 --> 00:41:58,110
all nonsense.

551
00:41:58,540 --> 00:42:00,210
She isn't my child.

552
00:42:01,250 --> 00:42:02,880
She's really my sister.

553
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:05,820
I know.

554
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,450
You said before that she was your sister.

555
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:11,720
Still,

556
00:42:12,460 --> 00:42:13,930
if people keep saying...

557
00:42:13,930 --> 00:42:16,630
If that's what you say, that's what it is.

558
00:42:17,730 --> 00:42:19,700
I believe only what you say.

559
00:42:28,170 --> 00:42:30,340
Don't believe a punk like me.

560
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:32,610
I'm a thug...

561
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:33,980
and uneducated.

562
00:42:34,350 --> 00:42:35,550
I'm going to believe you.

563
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:48,260
Hae Joo.

564
00:42:48,790 --> 00:42:50,130
Isn't this pretty?

565
00:42:52,760 --> 00:42:55,470
Young Choon made it for me.

566
00:42:55,470 --> 00:42:57,100
How pretty.

567
00:43:16,490 --> 00:43:18,560
Thank you, mister.

568
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:20,360
I told you, I'm not a "mister".

569
00:43:24,360 --> 00:43:27,070
Eng Cho. Let's tour Seoul.

570
00:44:17,150 --> 00:44:18,820
He finally got him.

571
00:44:18,820 --> 00:44:21,290
As soon as he gets up, he head-butts him.

572
00:44:21,620 --> 00:44:23,990
Head-butt. Yes.

573
00:44:30,060 --> 00:44:34,030
- Mom.
- You stayed at Eun Ja's?

574
00:44:34,030 --> 00:44:36,940
- Yes.
- You must've had fun.

575
00:44:37,100 --> 00:44:38,600
You're all smiles.

576
00:44:40,070 --> 00:44:41,410
I'll go to my room.

577
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:44,340
You brat.

578
00:44:48,810 --> 00:44:49,810
What?

579
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:58,590
Have you no fear? You went to Seoul?

580
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:02,190
How could you go there?

581
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:08,000
- How?
- Does Father know?

582
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:09,100
Father?

583
00:45:11,240 --> 00:45:12,440
So,

584
00:45:14,310 --> 00:45:16,510
you fear your father,

585
00:45:20,780 --> 00:45:21,850
but...

586
00:45:24,880 --> 00:45:26,050
your mom...

587
00:45:27,290 --> 00:45:28,820
is nothing?

588
00:45:29,250 --> 00:45:30,260
Is that it?

589
00:45:30,520 --> 00:45:31,520
Look.

590
00:45:31,690 --> 00:45:35,430
What would you have done if your father...

591
00:45:35,430 --> 00:45:37,900
wasn't at a funeral last night?

592
00:45:40,400 --> 00:45:41,600
He doesn't know?

593
00:45:42,430 --> 00:45:43,470
No.

594
00:45:43,970 --> 00:45:45,440
Your father doesn't know.

595
00:45:45,900 --> 00:45:46,970
Happy?

596
00:45:47,140 --> 00:45:48,610
Are you happy, you brat?

597
00:45:48,610 --> 00:45:52,510
You must be happy because
your father doesn't know.

598
00:45:52,510 --> 00:45:54,610
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

599
00:45:56,210 --> 00:45:57,920
You too.

600
00:45:59,750 --> 00:46:01,920
You're an adult.

601
00:46:02,490 --> 00:46:05,690
How could you scheme with
a kid and deceive me?

602
00:46:06,260 --> 00:46:07,430
What else...

603
00:46:08,660 --> 00:46:11,430
are you deceiving me about?

604
00:46:12,500 --> 00:46:14,000
What else...

605
00:46:14,470 --> 00:46:16,430
did you deceive me about?

606
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:18,570
Tell me!

607
00:46:18,640 --> 00:46:21,270
Mom, I'm sorry.

608
00:46:21,270 --> 00:46:23,210
Apologize to your father.

609
00:46:23,210 --> 00:46:24,740
Why are you apologizing to me?

610
00:46:24,740 --> 00:46:27,450
Your mom... Your mom is a moron.

611
00:46:27,450 --> 00:46:29,610
Why are you apologizing to me?

612
00:46:29,610 --> 00:46:31,320
- Mom!
- Please forgive us.

613
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:34,020
Mom! Stop it! You'll kill her!

614
00:46:34,020 --> 00:46:37,860
You know how much I trusted you.

615
00:46:39,290 --> 00:46:41,790
How could you lie to me...

616
00:46:41,790 --> 00:46:43,430
and stab me in the back?

617
00:46:43,430 --> 00:46:44,900
You brat!

618
00:46:44,900 --> 00:46:47,270
How could you do that to me?

619
00:46:47,270 --> 00:46:49,270
Let go. Let go!

620
00:46:49,870 --> 00:46:51,300
Let go!

621
00:46:53,240 --> 00:46:54,470
What's going on here?

622
00:46:56,510 --> 00:46:57,510
Hey.

623
00:46:58,980 --> 00:47:01,480
Why this old woman... You took on three?

624
00:47:01,480 --> 00:47:02,680
Are you a fighter?

625
00:47:03,210 --> 00:47:05,250
Are you?

626
00:47:10,190 --> 00:47:11,190
What?

627
00:47:12,420 --> 00:47:14,260
Are you glaring at me?

628
00:47:15,190 --> 00:47:16,190
Are you?

629
00:47:18,860 --> 00:47:21,370
Did you just glare at me?

630
00:47:23,270 --> 00:47:26,240
Look at her. Look at her being arrogant.

631
00:47:29,740 --> 00:47:31,610
What did you do wrong this time?

632
00:47:31,610 --> 00:47:32,810
It's nothing.

633
00:47:32,810 --> 00:47:34,180
Nothing? Then...

634
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:38,180
Jung Hee. Did you get into trouble again?

635
00:47:38,980 --> 00:47:41,320
No. Definitely not.

636
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:43,320
Look at that brat.

637
00:47:45,490 --> 00:47:46,860
Are you hurt?

638
00:47:46,860 --> 00:47:48,830
No, I'm fine.

639
00:47:50,530 --> 00:47:52,230
Seriously.

640
00:48:02,010 --> 00:48:04,040
What's with you lately?

641
00:48:04,780 --> 00:48:07,580
Did something go wrong at your gathering?

642
00:48:09,650 --> 00:48:11,150
No, it did not.

643
00:48:13,180 --> 00:48:14,750
Look at her.

644
00:48:15,250 --> 00:48:16,760
Her master is talking,

645
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,660
but she doesn't even look.

646
00:48:20,530 --> 00:48:22,860
Master? How are you my master?

647
00:48:23,460 --> 00:48:24,500
Then what?

648
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:28,630
Are you the master of the house and I am...

649
00:48:28,630 --> 00:48:29,970
the servant or something?

650
00:48:31,670 --> 00:48:33,170
What is wrong with you?

651
00:48:34,810 --> 00:48:36,070
Forget it. Stop it.

652
00:48:37,440 --> 00:48:39,840
What? You slept over?

653
00:48:39,840 --> 00:48:41,810
You slept in Jin's room?

654
00:48:43,280 --> 00:48:44,750
It's so romantic.

655
00:48:44,750 --> 00:48:46,080
You must've been so happy.

656
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:47,150
- You just slept?
- Hey.

657
00:48:48,220 --> 00:48:49,220
Step aside.

658
00:48:52,420 --> 00:48:53,860
What's wrong with her?

659
00:48:53,860 --> 00:48:56,130
- Hae Joo?
- That's right.

660
00:48:56,430 --> 00:48:59,730
You know that thug, Young Choon?

661
00:48:59,730 --> 00:49:00,870
- I do.
- I do.

662
00:49:00,870 --> 00:49:04,300
I saw her and him laughing and smiling...

663
00:49:04,440 --> 00:49:05,540
