664
00:49:05,540 --> 00:49:07,770
No way.

665
00:49:08,470 --> 00:49:10,080
Seriously.

666
00:49:10,080 --> 00:49:11,380
Who...

667
00:49:13,380 --> 00:49:14,610
Hey, Gwi Ja.

668
00:49:15,780 --> 00:49:18,950
I told you not to run
your big mouth, right?

669
00:49:18,950 --> 00:49:21,250
What did I do?

670
00:49:21,750 --> 00:49:24,760
I only spoke the truth about what I saw.

671
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:28,430
They brought the kid and swung their arms,

672
00:49:28,430 --> 00:49:29,960
having fun.

673
00:49:29,960 --> 00:49:31,660
What? A kid?

674
00:49:31,660 --> 00:49:32,660
Yes.

675
00:49:33,270 --> 00:49:34,270
Hae Joo.

676
00:49:36,130 --> 00:49:37,800
Do you have a kid?

677
00:49:39,370 --> 00:49:40,370
What?

678
00:49:42,270 --> 00:49:43,410
Hey, Hae Joo.

679
00:49:45,340 --> 00:49:46,440
Didn't I...

680
00:49:47,310 --> 00:49:50,780
tell you to stay away from Young Choon?

681
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:54,350
Do you like him?

682
00:49:56,390 --> 00:49:57,960
Hae Joo, let's go.

683
00:50:00,760 --> 00:50:02,060
Do you like him?

684
00:50:03,030 --> 00:50:04,030
Yes,

685
00:50:05,430 --> 00:50:06,500
I like him.

686
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:09,270
- She's lost her mind.
- Oh my gosh.

687
00:50:09,270 --> 00:50:10,940
It's true.

688
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:12,500
Why you...

689
00:50:12,500 --> 00:50:15,170
- Hey!
- Stop!

690
00:50:15,170 --> 00:50:16,710
Freeze!

691
00:50:18,380 --> 00:50:24,120
Freeze!

692
00:50:34,630 --> 00:50:37,400
Do you think the classroom
is a place for sparring?

693
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:39,460
How dare you fight here?

694
00:50:40,600 --> 00:50:42,300
Hae Joo, that witch,

695
00:50:42,730 --> 00:50:44,770
keeps hitting on Young Choon.

696
00:50:44,770 --> 00:50:47,640
Ae Sook. Don't make accusations like that.

697
00:50:47,640 --> 00:50:49,840
You're jealous too. Don't pretend.

698
00:50:49,840 --> 00:50:51,980
Hae Joo and Young Choon are...

699
00:50:52,140 --> 00:50:53,680
Ae Sook.

700
00:50:56,680 --> 00:50:57,750
All of you,

701
00:50:58,820 --> 00:51:00,050
turn around.

702
00:51:06,060 --> 00:51:08,060
You're wearing strappy undershirts?

703
00:51:08,490 --> 00:51:11,260
Don't you know they're banned?

704
00:51:12,130 --> 00:51:14,170
Darn it.

705
00:51:14,170 --> 00:51:17,370
Why is she suddenly complaining about it?

706
00:51:17,740 --> 00:51:19,440
She's just jealous.

707
00:51:24,180 --> 00:51:25,280
Move it.

708
00:51:27,450 --> 00:51:29,350
Let's clean quietly.

709
00:51:29,450 --> 00:51:31,480
I don't want to run laps again.

710
00:51:41,460 --> 00:51:44,130
The early morning rain

711
00:51:44,260 --> 00:51:46,160
Wets the rails

712
00:51:53,810 --> 00:51:55,970
The early morning rain

713
00:51:56,010 --> 00:51:58,010
Wets the roof

714
00:52:00,210 --> 00:52:02,210
It leaves an echo

715
00:52:02,250 --> 00:52:05,820
And it really leaves

716
00:52:08,550 --> 00:52:12,260
The early morning rain wets the rails

717
00:52:13,020 --> 00:52:15,430
Dong Moon is on probation?

718
00:52:15,430 --> 00:52:19,230
That's right. A police
station from Seoul called.

719
00:52:19,230 --> 00:52:21,470
He was caught violating curfew.

720
00:52:24,300 --> 00:52:26,810
So he has to write
apologies after school...

721
00:52:27,170 --> 00:52:29,940
and can't tutor us for a while.

722
00:52:38,350 --> 00:52:39,550
Dong Moon.

723
00:52:42,950 --> 00:52:44,790
Why didn't you tell me...

724
00:52:45,320 --> 00:52:47,360
you were at the police station?

725
00:52:48,660 --> 00:52:51,100
Bong Soo, that punk. I said not to tell.

726
00:52:53,530 --> 00:52:54,670
Go.

727
00:52:55,200 --> 00:52:57,740
Sorry. It's my fault.

728
00:52:59,300 --> 00:53:02,170
No need. I'm the one that went after you.

729
00:53:02,770 --> 00:53:03,940
I was an idiot.

730
00:53:05,340 --> 00:53:07,950
Still, I'm sorry.

731
00:53:08,410 --> 00:53:11,720
You need to act in order to learn.

732
00:53:12,650 --> 00:53:14,350
That's what my dad said.

733
00:53:15,020 --> 00:53:16,290
He was right.

734
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:18,660
I had to do something stupid...

735
00:53:19,560 --> 00:53:21,930
to learn what can't be, can't be.

736
00:53:23,190 --> 00:53:24,360
Get home safely.

737
00:53:29,470 --> 00:53:30,670
Dong Moon!

738
00:53:37,410 --> 00:53:38,540
Jung Hee.

739
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:43,320
How heartbreaking.

740
00:53:48,190 --> 00:53:49,790
Do you like Jin that much?

741
00:53:59,360 --> 00:54:00,500
Young Choon?

742
00:54:00,930 --> 00:54:02,000
Yes.

743
00:54:02,000 --> 00:54:04,940
You know that Seoul girl, Park Hae Joo?

744
00:54:04,970 --> 00:54:06,240
The professor's daughter.

745
00:54:07,010 --> 00:54:10,380
I hear they're going around dating.

746
00:54:11,180 --> 00:54:12,880
Everyone in town...

747
00:54:13,180 --> 00:54:15,410
is talking about it.

748
00:54:15,410 --> 00:54:16,480
Really?

749
00:54:18,980 --> 00:54:21,720
What was that? Who's dating? Us?

750
00:54:21,920 --> 00:54:24,620
Do you think that arrogant Seoul girl...

751
00:54:24,920 --> 00:54:26,930
would give me a second thought?

752
00:54:26,930 --> 00:54:28,590
Right? No, right?

753
00:54:30,030 --> 00:54:31,600
I told you.

754
00:54:36,430 --> 00:54:37,600
Mister.

755
00:54:41,370 --> 00:54:42,670
Hello, miss.

756
00:54:45,410 --> 00:54:49,010
The professor needs the
chimney fixed, right?

757
00:54:50,580 --> 00:54:51,650
Let's go.

758
00:54:54,520 --> 00:54:55,590
You're leaving?

759
00:54:57,060 --> 00:54:58,190
Where to?

760
00:54:59,290 --> 00:55:02,590
There's a job opening in Busan.

761
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:04,600
So...

762
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:07,430
don't talk to me...

763
00:55:08,300 --> 00:55:09,670
until I leave.

764
00:55:10,100 --> 00:55:11,570
Don't look at me either.

765
00:55:11,900 --> 00:55:13,670
That's not right.

766
00:55:14,540 --> 00:55:17,480
You're doing this because
people are talking, right?

767
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:20,280
Who cares what people think?

768
00:55:22,410 --> 00:55:25,320
Regardless. Don't come to
the pharmacy anymore...

769
00:55:25,950 --> 00:55:27,490
either.

770
00:55:28,790 --> 00:55:30,620
- No.
- Listen to me.

771
00:55:32,390 --> 00:55:33,490
You'll...

772
00:55:34,560 --> 00:55:35,890
regret it.

773
00:55:36,830 --> 00:55:39,100
- No.
- Then what?

774
00:55:39,630 --> 00:55:40,770
No.

775
00:55:48,410 --> 00:55:49,640
Hey, Seoul Chick.

776
00:55:50,540 --> 00:55:52,680
Are you being arrogant just because...

777
00:55:54,080 --> 00:55:55,410
I hung out with you a little?

778
00:55:55,780 --> 00:55:58,480
You still don't get it?

779
00:56:07,590 --> 00:56:10,360
I'm not interested in you anymore.

780
00:56:38,360 --> 00:56:39,460
Dong Moon.

781
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:42,660
Why do you keep getting on my mind?

782
00:56:57,880 --> 00:57:00,480
I'm not interested in you anymore.

783
00:57:36,080 --> 00:57:37,180
Who is it?

784
00:57:38,880 --> 00:57:40,020
What's up?

785
00:57:44,860 --> 00:57:45,920
Joo Young Choon?

786
00:57:52,430 --> 00:57:54,230
Who are you?

787
00:57:55,470 --> 00:57:56,500
- What...
- Mister.

788
00:57:57,270 --> 00:57:58,800
Talk to me. Let go.

789
00:57:58,970 --> 00:58:00,610
- Stay still.
- I didn't do anything.

790
00:58:01,340 --> 00:58:04,280
Wait a minute. Mister. What's going on?

791
00:58:04,780 --> 00:58:05,780
Mister.

792
00:58:09,980 --> 00:58:11,080
Mister.

793
00:58:12,850 --> 00:58:14,950
Mister.

794
00:58:15,820 --> 00:58:16,860
Mister.

795
00:58:21,690 --> 00:58:22,860
Mister.

796
00:58:39,280 --> 00:58:40,550
Guess.

797
00:58:40,980 --> 00:58:42,150
Come on.

798
00:58:44,850 --> 00:58:47,750
Okay. Let's start.

799
00:58:52,690 --> 00:58:54,230
Hae Joo isn't here yet?

800
00:58:56,290 --> 00:58:57,330
No.

801
00:58:58,230 --> 00:58:59,560
That's odd.

802
00:58:59,930 --> 00:59:01,700
No one's answering the phone.

803
00:59:02,470 --> 00:59:04,500
Okay. Page 83.

804
00:59:13,750 --> 00:59:14,810
Hae Joo!

805
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:18,050
Hae Joo!

806
00:59:27,030 --> 00:59:28,430
Where did she go?

807
00:59:34,200 --> 00:59:36,300
Olivia won't pick up?

808
00:59:36,970 --> 00:59:38,640
- No.
- Really?

809
00:59:38,870 --> 00:59:41,470
Maybe the phone is broken. Hello?

810
00:59:42,970 --> 00:59:44,010
Is it broken?

811
00:59:46,380 --> 00:59:49,080
Is Dong Moon still on probation?

812
00:59:49,080 --> 00:59:50,080
Yes.

813
00:59:50,720 --> 00:59:53,050
Gosh. That poor thing.

814
00:59:53,050 --> 00:59:55,290
I kind of miss him, don't you?

815
00:59:55,750 --> 00:59:57,790
I'm good at adding and subtracting now.

816
00:59:57,790 --> 00:59:59,760
I want to study.

817
01:00:03,700 --> 01:00:05,900
What is this uneasy feeling?

818
01:00:06,600 --> 01:00:08,330
Hae Joo and Dong Moon...

819
01:00:44,170 --> 01:00:45,270
It's raining.

820
01:00:59,150 --> 01:01:01,650
- Jung Hee.
- You wrote your apology?

821
01:01:03,020 --> 01:01:04,020
I did.

822
01:01:05,960 --> 01:01:09,160
I told you not to come.

823
01:01:09,730 --> 01:01:11,260
How could I not?

824
01:01:11,800 --> 01:01:14,030
My friend was going to walk in the rain.

825
01:01:14,130 --> 01:01:16,370
- We're friends.
- Friends?

826
01:01:22,710 --> 01:01:24,210
I don't want to be friends either now.

827
01:01:25,240 --> 01:01:26,280
Go home.

828
01:01:27,280 --> 01:01:29,010
You lent me your umbrella before too.

829
01:01:29,250 --> 01:01:32,780
I'm paying you back. I hate owing a debt.

830
01:01:37,120 --> 01:01:38,120
Jung Hee.

831
01:01:38,890 --> 01:01:39,890
Yes?

832
01:01:40,530 --> 01:01:41,660
Don't do this.

833
01:01:49,900 --> 01:01:51,340
Hey, Dong Moon!

834
01:01:57,580 --> 01:01:58,580
Jung Hee.

835
01:01:59,140 --> 01:02:01,480
Don't walk in the rain.
You'll catch a cold.

836
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:03,750
Don't mind me!

837
01:02:04,220 --> 01:02:06,720
Whether I get wet or catch a cold,

838
01:02:06,890 --> 01:02:08,490
what's it to you?

839
01:02:08,920 --> 01:02:10,460
You said we aren't even friends.

840
01:02:22,930 --> 01:02:25,470
(Tune in for the final episode.)
